-- CNPC's Fuel Sales to Increase 30% to 100 Million Tons This Year From 2005
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-26T00:23:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-26/cnpc-s-fuel-sales-to-increase-30-to-100-million-tons-this-year-from-2005.html
China National Petroleum Corp.’s
fuel sales will rise 30 percent to 100 million metric tons this
year from 2005, the company said in its online newsletter today.
CNPC’s share of retail fuel sales in China will reach more than
43 percent in 2010, according to the Beijing-based company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
